# Admin/System-Admin Web Quality Gate

- Trigger: when `import.meta.env.MODE` is `admin` or `system-admin`.
- Goal: deliver desktop backoffice UX with clear business logic, not mobile-style shell pages.

## Must-Have Structure

- Desktop layout required: side navigation + top bar + content area.
- At least one core data table/list with filters and detail view per page.
- No bottom mobile tab bar in backoffice desktop mode.
- Default landing view must be backoffice dashboard/console, not customer home.

## Business Logic Minimum

- Every module defines: key KPI cards, primary action, and state transition feedback.
- Include permission-aware rendering (`customer`, `lobby_manager`, `admin`, `system_admin`).
- Include loading, empty, error, and unauthorized states for interactive blocks.

## Delivery Gate (cannot skip)

- Map screen sections to PRD goals before implementation.
- Run and verify:
  - `pnpm --filter customer-web lint`
  - `pnpm --filter customer-web type-check`
  - `pnpm --filter customer-web build`
- Demo scripts must be validated with clean ports and expected URLs.
